item.title: No-ip
item.dc:creator: @owner_Ethan owner Ethan
item.description:
@owner_Ethan wrote:

[quote=“blitz_9100, post:4, topic:29475”]do you have a router? if so then please then goto start and click run and type cmd and click ok then make sure its in the windows directory or system32 and type this in ipconfig/all,if you dont have it in that directory then type
cd C:\WINDOWS\system32 after that you should get some colums with lots of numbers in it.then go down until you see Default Gateway then copy the default gateway by right click mark then goto the bar at the top and right click copy then past that ip in your address bar.then you should get a screen asking for your password.if you dont know and havent set it then try admin for pass first then try admin for username and pass.then find gaming tab of whatever portfowarding.then click it and enter your ip(get it from the cmd prompt you did earlier should be IP Address) then the port of your server then the ending port(the same as the port for your server)then check enable.then try to see if anyone can connect[/quote]
You do notice people have different routers right?
